+# OmniCode — Universal Code Workspace
+
+**OmniCode** is a fork of [T3 Code](https://github.com/pingdotgg/t3code) that extends its AI-native development philosophy into a universal, extensible, multi-provider coding platform. This specification describes the architecture, plugin system, API integrations, AI agent framework, and UI extension model that define OmniCode.
+
+---
+
+## Vision & Philosophy
+
+### Why OmniCode Exists
+
+T3 Code proved that AI-native coding in the terminal is not only possible but transformative. However, real-world software development involves far more than chatting with an LLM: developers navigate repositories across multiple hosting providers, triage issues, review pull requests, manage worktrees, and increasingly rely on automated agents for code review and issue management.
+
+OmniCode extends T3 Code from a single-provider AI chat interface into an **open platform** where:
+
+- Developers can browse repos, search issues, and review PRs across **any Git hosting provider** from one unified UI.
+- **AI agents** — code reviewers, issue triagers, auto-fix agents — operate as first-class citizens alongside the chat interface.
+- **Third-party plugins** can contribute new providers, agents, UI panels, and lifecycle hooks without modifying OmniCode core.
+- Everything is built on **Effect** — the same typed, composable, error-aware foundation that makes T3 Code reliable.
+
+### Core Tenets
+
+1. **Provider Paradise** — Every Git hosting provider (GitHub, GitLab, Bitbucket, Gitea, Azure DevOps) speaks the same `SourceControlProviderShape` interface. Users are never locked in.
+2. **Extensibility First** — The plugin system is not an afterthought; it's a first-class architectural primitive. Any behavior can be contributed, overridden, or replaced.
+3. **Agents as Plugins** — AI agents are just plugins that implement the `Agent` base class. They register themselves, declare capabilities, and are discovered and orchestrated automatically.
+4. **All Contracts Are Public** — Every schema, service interface, and extension point is exported from `@omnicode/contracts`. Nothing is hidden.
+5. **Performance & Reliability** — Inherited from T3 Code: Effect's typed errors, structured concurrency, and resource-safe patterns are used throughout.
+
+### Design Inspirations
+
+| Influence | How It Shaped OmniCode |
+|-----------|----------------------|
+| **VSCode Extension API** | Plugin manifests, contribution points, activation events, and the lifecycle pattern |
+| **Vim/Neovim Plugin Ecosystem** | Decentralized discovery, plugin markers in package.json, hook-based extensibility |
+| **GitHub CLI (`gh`)** | Octokit-backed services mirror `gh` commands but as composable Effect programs |
+| **LangChain / AI SDKs** | Agent base class with lifecycle hooks, registry dispatch, typed I/O |
+| **Obsidian / Dataview** | Paints (UI decorations) that inject before/after/append/prepend at named targets |
+| **T3 Code's Effect Architecture** | `Context.Service`, `Layer`, `Schema` — all OmniCode services follow the same patterns |
+
+---
+
+## Architecture Overview
+
