+## GitHub Integration API
+
+### Octokit Client (`GitHubClient.ts`)
+
+The `GitHubClient` wraps `@octokit/rest` and integrates it with Effect's error handling and dependency injection patterns.
+
+#### Authentication Modes
+
+```typescript
+export type GitHubAuthConfig =
+  | GitHubTokenAuth      // { _tag: "token", token: string }
+  | GitHubAppAuth        // { _tag: "app", appId, privateKey, installationId? }
+  | GitHubOAuthAuth;     // { _tag: "oauth", clientId, clientSecret, code }
+```
+
+#### Error Classification
+
+Octokit errors are mapped to Effect `Data.TaggedError` variants:
+
+| HTTP Status | Error Type | Description |
+|-------------|------------|-------------|
+| `401` | `GitHubAuthError` | Authentication failure |
+| `404` | `GitHubNotFoundError` | Resource not found |
+| `403 / 429` | `GitHubRateLimitError` | Rate limit hit (includes `retryAfter`) |
+| Other | `GitHubApiError` | Generic API error (includes `operation`, `status`) |
+
+#### Service Pattern
+
+All services follow the same structure:
+
+1. **Domain Types** — Raw domain interfaces (e.g., `GitHubIssue`, `PullRequestDetail`)
+2. **Service Shape** — Interface with Effect-typed methods
+3. **Service Tag** — `Context.Service<...>("@omnicode/github/ServiceName")`
+4. **Mappers** — Functions converting Octokit snake_case response data to camelCase domain types
+5. **Constructor** — `make` that maps over `GitHubClient` and returns the shape
+6. **Layer** — `layer = Layer.effect(ServiceTag, make)`
+
+### Services
+
+#### `IssuesService`
+
+| Method | Octokit API | Description |
+|--------|------------|-------------|
+| `getIssue(owner, repo, number)` | `issues.get` | Get a single issue |
+| `createIssue(input)` | `issues.create` | Create a new issue |
+| `updateIssue(input)` | `issues.update` | Update an existing issue |
+| `listIssues(input)` | `issues.listForRepo` | List issues with filters |
+| `searchIssues(input)` | `search.issuesAndPullRequests` | Full-text issue search |
+| `listComments(owner, repo, number)` | `issues.listComments` | List comments on an issue |
+| `createComment(input)` | `issues.createComment` | Add a comment to an issue |
