+## AI Agent Lifecycle
+
+### Agent Base Class (`Agent.ts`)
+
+All agents extend `Agent<TInput, TOutput>` and follow a strict lifecycle:
+
+```
+run(input)
+  │
+  ├─ initialize(input)        // Setup: load models, validate config
+  ├─ execute(input)           // Core logic (abstract — must implement)
+  ├─ complete(output)         // Post-processing: logging, notifications
+  └─ cleanup()                // Teardown: always called, even on error
+         │
+         └─ Returns AgentResult<TOutput>
+```
+
+#### Lifecycle States
+
+```typescript
+type AgentLifecycle =
+  | "idle"          // Constructed, not yet run
+  | "initializing"  // initialize() in progress
+  | "ready"         // Initialized, about to execute
+  | "running"       // execute() in progress
+  | "completed"     // execute + complete successful
+  | "failed"        // Error thrown during lifecycle
+  | "cleanedUp";    // cleanup() called (final state)
+```
+
+#### AgentResult
+
+```typescript
+export interface AgentResult<TOutput = unknown> {
+  readonly agent: AgentType;
+  readonly success: boolean;
+  readonly output: TOutput;
+  readonly durationMs: number;
+  readonly error?: string;
+}
+```
+
+### Code Review Flow
+
+The `CodeReviewAgent` analyzes PR diffs and produces structured feedback:
+
+```
+CodeReviewAgent.execute(context: ReviewContext)
+  │
+  ├─ context contains: repo, prNumber, title, description,
+  │                    files (FileChange[]), existingComments, branches
+  │
+  ├─ For each file in context.files:
+  │   ├─ Split diff into lines
+  │   └─ For each pattern (built-in + extra):
+  │       └─ If pattern.test(file, lines) matches:
+  │           └─ Create ReviewComment (filePath, line, severity, message, suggestion)
+  │
+  ├─ Deduplicate comments by (filePath, line, rule)
+  └─ Return ReviewOutput { summary, comments, filesReviewed, issuesFound }
+```
+
+#### Built-in Detection Patterns
+
+| Severity | Rule | What It Detects |
+|----------|------|-----------------|
+| `warning` | `no-console-log` | `console.log()` / `console.debug()` calls |
+| `error` | `no-debugger` | `debugger` statements |
+| `warning` | `no-todo` | `// TODO` comments |
+| `error` | `no-inner-html` | `.innerHTML =` assignments (XSS risk) |
+| `warning` | `sql-injection-risk` | Raw SQL string interpolation |
+| `info` | `large-dependency-import` | Importing entire `lodash` |
+| `warning` | `no-any` | TypeScript `: any` usage |
+| `info` | `long-function` | Diff hunks exceeding 100 lines |
+
+Plugins can add patterns via `addPatterns(...patterns)` or by extending `CodeReviewAgent`.
+
+### Issue Triage Flow
+
+The `IssueTriageAgent` classifies incoming issues and suggests labels, assignees, and priority:
+
+```
+IssueTriageAgent.execute(context: TriageContext)
+  │
+  ├─ context contains: repo, issueNumber, title, body,
+  │                    existingLabels, author
+  │
+  ├─ Score each ClassificationRule against title + body:
+  │   └─ For each pattern in rule, if regex matches → increment score
+  │
+  ├─ Select best-matching rule (highest score)
+  ├─ If no match → default to "other" type
+  │
+  ├─ Build TriageOutput:
+  │   ├─ issueType: "bug" | "feature" | "enhancement" | "documentation"
+  │   │             | "question" | "refactor" | "performance" | "security" | "other"
+  │   ├─ suggestedLabels: existing labels + matched rule label
+  │   ├─ suggestedAssignees: based on priority/type heuristics
+  │   ├─ priority: "critical" | "high" | "medium" | "low"
+  │   ├─ confidence: 0.0–1.0 based on match score
+  │   └─ reasoning: human-readable explanation
+  └─ Return TriageOutput
+```
+
+#### Classification Rules
+
+| Type | Trigger Patterns | Default Priority |
+|------|-----------------|-----------------|
+| `bug` | bug, crash, error, broken, regression | `high` |
+| `feature` | feature, request, implement, proposal | `medium` |
+| `enhancement` | improve, optimize, enhance | `medium` |
+| `documentation` | docs, documentation, readme, typo | `low` |
+| `question` | question, how, why, help | `low` |
+| `performance` | performance, slow, latency, leak | `medium` |
+| `security` | security, vulnerability, xss, cve | `critical` |
+| `refactor` | refactor, cleanup, tech debt | `low` |
+
+### Agent Registry & Orchestrator
+
+The `AgentRegistry` is the central dispatch point:
+
+```typescript
+export class AgentRegistry {
+  register<TInput, TOutput>(agent: Agent<TInput, TOutput>): this;
+  registerOrReplace<TInput, TOutput>(agent: Agent<TInput, TOutput>): this;
+  unregister(type: AgentType): boolean;
+  get<TInput, TOutput>(type: AgentType): Agent<TInput, TOutput> | undefined;
+  require<TInput, TOutput>(type: AgentType): Agent<TInput, TOutput>;
+  dispatch<TInput, TOutput>(type: AgentType, input: TInput): Promise<AgentResult<TOutput>>;
+  listTypes(): AgentType[];
+  listAgents(): AgentDescriptor[];
+  clear(): void;
+}
+```
+
+The **orchestrator** (planned — server-level integration) will:
+
+1. Subscribe to plugin hooks (e.g., `"pr:created"`)
+2. Look up registered agents by capability (e.g., agents with `"code-review"` capability)
+3. Build the appropriate context (e.g., `ReviewContext` from PR data)
+4. Call `registry.dispatch("code-review", context)`
+5. Post results back to the provider (e.g., submit review comments to the PR)
+6. Emit `"agent:after_run"` hook for downstream plugins
+
+### Agent Capabilities
+
+```typescript
+type AgentCapability =
+  | "code-review"
+  | "issue-triage"
+  | "pr-analysis"
+  | "code-generation"
+  | "testing"
+  | "documentation"
+  | "security-analysis";
+```
