+
+## Worktrees
+
+OmniCode inherits T3 Code's full **git worktree** implementation, which is already production-ready in the base. T3 Code provides:
+
+### Worktree Branch Prefix
+
+```typescript
+// From packages/shared/src/git.ts
+export const WORKTREE_BRANCH_PREFIX = "t3code";
+```
+
+Worktree branches follow the pattern `t3code/<random-8-char-hex>` and are managed automatically.
+
+### T3 Code Worktree Operations (Inherited)
+
+| Operation | Description | Implementation Location |
+|-----------|-------------|------------------------|
+| **Create** | Create a linked worktree for isolated development | `apps/web/src/lib/sourceControlActions.ts` |
+| **List** | List all linked worktrees | `packages/shared/src/git.ts` (git worktree list) |
+| **Remove** | Prune and remove a worktree | `apps/web/src/lib/chatThreadActions.ts` |
+| **Cleanup** | Automatic stale worktree cleanup | `apps/web/src/worktreeCleanup.test.ts` |
+| **Branch sanitization** | Sanitize user input into valid Git ref names | `packages/shared/src/git.ts` |
+
+### How OmniCode Uses Worktrees
+
+OmniCode extends the worktree system for multi-provider workflows:
+
+1. **PR-Focused Worktrees** — When a user checks out a PR from any provider (GitHub/GitLab/etc.), OmniCode creates a worktree for isolated review and testing.
+2. **Agent Worktrees** — AI agents can create temporary worktrees to test fixes, apply patches, or create PR branches without disrupting the user's primary workspace.
+3. **Provider-Agnostic Worktrees** — Worktree creation works identically regardless of which Git hosting provider the repository is linked to.
+4. **Cleanup Integration** — The worktree cleanup subsystem integrates with the plugin hook system so plugins can react to worktree lifecycle events.
+
+### Worktree Data Flow (Agent Use Case)
+
+```
+User says "review PR #42 from octocat/Hello-World"
+  │
+  ├─ Orchestrator checks: is there an active worktree? → No
+  ├─ Creates worktree (git worktree add)
+  ├─ Fetches PR files via PullRequestsService
+  ├─ Runs CodeReviewAgent on file diffs
+  ├─ Submits review via ReviewsService
+  └─ Optionally removes worktree (or leaves for user inspection)
+```
